---
By: The Upanishads
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 491
    Verse: 20
Tags:
  - Wisdom
---
The sage must distinguish between knowledge and wisdom. Knowledge is of
things, acts and relations. But wisdom is of God alone; and, beyond all
things, acts, and relations, it abides forever. To become one with God is
the only wisdom.
